<HEAD>Armand Hammer Celebrates 91st Birthday With Wishes From Around the
World</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto LA8</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 550 guests sang the praises of Armand
Hammer on the 91st birthday of the philanthropist and chairman of
Occidental Petroleum Corp.
   The party at the Beverly Hilton Hotel on Sunday night included
performances by the Los Angeles Philharmonic with cellist Mstislav
Rostropovich and violinist Issac Stern accompanied by baritone
Sherill Milnes.
   Host Danny Thomas read congratulatory wires to Hammer from
President and Mrs. Bush, Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev, French
President Francois Mitterand and his wife Danielle, Israeli Prime
Minister Yitzhak Shamir, King Constantine of Greece and the Duke
and Duchess of York.
   The birthday toast to Hammer was given by entertainer Helen
Hayes. Hammer had a crush on the actress 56 years ago, when ``I was
35 and you were much, much younger,'' he told the her and the crowd.
   ``My dreams _ to create a meaningful peace in a world free of
nuclear weapons and the defeat of cancer in my lifetime _ are
closer to reality than ever before, '' Hammer said.
   Hammer throughout many of the Cold War years was a leading
advocate of improved relations with the Soviets.
