<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     05-29 0435</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0446</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tornado Strikes Nebraska, Snow Falls in Montana</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms rumbled across the Midwest early today, while snow
fell on parts of Montana.
   Rainshowers and thunderstorms struck eastern and south-central
Nebraska and western Iowa this morning.
   Early morning thunderstorms damaged a high school building at
Millard, Neb. On Sunday evening, a tornado touched down near
Juniata, Neb., and tennis ball-size hail fell near Ulysses.
   Rain changed to snow this morning over parts of Montana, where
earlier storms dumped as much as 10 inches of snow near Cutbank and
East Glacier. Slightly more than an inch of snow fell at Great
Falls Sunday evening to bring its snowfall total for the season
ending June 30 to a record 107 inches.
   Elsewhere, showers fell on parts of Illinois, Idaho, Wyoming,
North Dakota and Kentucky and from the northern Pacific coast into
northern California.
   Heavier rainfall during the 6 hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included nearly an inch at Belleville, Ill.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
over the Great Lakes, the upper and middle Mississippi Valley,
eastern parts of the central Plains and South Dakota; scattered
showers over the northern Plains, the northern Rockies and the
northern Pacific Coast; and strong winds across the central Rockies.
   Highs were expected to be in the 40s, 50s and 60s over western
and central Montana, the Pacific Northwest, the northern Rockies,
the northern Plains, northern Minnesota, upper Michigan and along
the Pacific Coast; in the 90s in the desert Southwest, the southern
Rockies, the southern Plains, Kansas, the lower Missouri and
Mississippi valleys, the Tennessee Valley and the Gulf Coast; and
in the 70s and 80s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 32
degrees at Great Falls, Mont., to 82 degrees at Phoenix and Del
Rio, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 66 fair; Boston 55 fair; Buffalo 43 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 68 fair; Cincinnati 63 partly cloudy; Cleveland 52
fair; Detroit 50 fair; Miami 81 fair; New York 58 fair;
Philadelphia 51 fair; Pittsburgh 50 fair; Portland, Maine 43 fair;
Washington 56 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 44 7 thunderstorms; Chicago 61 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 76 cloudy; Denver 60 fair; Des Moines 59
thunderstorms; Indianapolis 60 cloudy; Kansas City 72 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 61 cloudy; Nashville 64 cloudy; New Orleans 77
fair; St. Louis 60 windy.
   _West: Albuquerque 72 fair; Anchorage 50 rain; Las Vegas 71
windy; Los Angeles 58 fair; Phoenix 81 fair; Salt Lake City 52
windy; San Diego 62 cloudy; San Francisco 52 windy; Seattle 49 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 52 fair; Toronto 50 fair.
