<HEAD>Tickets to Mass Sold For $160 on Black Market</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HELSINKI, Finland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tickets for a Mass to be celebrated by
Pope John Paul in Finland next week are being sold on the black
market for about $160, reports said Monday.
   The Roman Catholic Church condemned the scalpers, saying all
7,900 tickets it has given out were free.
   ``There are still about 1,000 people on the waiting list for the
holy mass,'' church authorities said.
   There are 4,200 Catholics in Finland, according to figures
published by the Catholic Information Bureau.
   The pope is scheduled to visit Finland June 4-6 during a tour
that also takes him to Norway, Iceland, Denmark and Sweden.
   It will be the first papal visit to this predominantly Lutheran
country where 88 percent of the population of 4.9 million belong to
the national church.
