<HEAD>East German Border Guard Escapes to West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 20-year-old East German border
guard abandoned his weapon and climbed over a steel-mesh fence to
escape to West Germany, police said Monday.
   The soldier ``waited until his supervisor was temporarily gone,
then abandoned his sub-machinegun and climbed over the steel-mesh
fence to escape,'' the Bavarian border police said.
   The escape near the Bavarian city of Coburg occurred Friday,
police said.
   Ten-foot-high chain-link fences constructed by the East Germans
separate the two German nations along their border near Coburg.
   Coburg is about 120 miles north of the Bavarian capital, Munich.
