<HEAD>Policeman Dies of Wounds Suffered in Riots</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A policeman sent to help quell last week's
riots in the central Nigerian city of Benin has died of gunshot
wounds, a newspaper reported Monday.
   The Times said the officer was shot in the head Friday by a
rioter using a hunting rifle and died Sunday night in a government
hospital, according to the Lagos Times.
   Five civilians died in the three days of unrest, which were
touched off by students protesting government economic reforms.
   The Times said police and soldiers still were patrolling Benin
and guarding a refinery and petrochemical plant in the nearby town
of Warri.
