been compared to the U.S. military involvement in Vietnam.
   Wheeler said Orlov and Vishnyakov told him that when they return
to the Soviet Union they hope to convince the Soviet government to
establish a similar monument in Moscow honoring the Soviet dead in
Afghanistan.
   The Soviet Union was a chief provider of supplies and weapons
for the North Vietnamese and Viet Cong during the Vietnam War.
