<FIRST>r i AM-Iran-Khomeini     05-29 0305</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Iran-Khomeini,0316</SECOND>
<HEAD>Khomeini Recuperating, Visited by Family</HEAD>
<HEAD>Laserphoto TEH-2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tehran radio said Monday that Iranian
leader Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini is making satisfactory progress
after undergoing surgery to stop bleeding in the digestive system.
   Iranian television showed the 86-year-old Shiite Moslem patriach
being visited by relatives at a hospital. The surgery was performed
last Tuesday.
   The television announcer reported that Khomeini suffered a
slight heart complication on Saturday. It gave no details but said
the condition was ``relieved'' on Sunday.
   Iran's main opposition group, the Iraq-based Mujahedeen Khalq,
said in a message to The Associated Press in Cyprus that Khomeini
had suffered a heart attack Saturday. The assertion could not be
independently verified.
   The Tehran radio broadcast, monitored in Nicosia, said
Khomeini's digestive system is now functioning normally and he is
being served solid foods.
   Iranian television showed Khomeini in a hospital bed with his
son Ahmad sitting nearby. It also showd Ahmad Khomeini's young son
playing with a stethoscope and climbing onto the high hospital bed
to kiss his grandfather.
   Khomeini, receiving medication through an intravenous tube, was
propped up in the bed with a food tray in front of him.
   Relatives were shown coaxing him through each spoonful as he was
fed what appeared to be abgoosht, a soup consisting of the broth
from boiled meat and potatoes.
   Some dates and bread were on the tray, but the television did
not show Khomeini eating them.
   Khomeini's personal physician said after the operation in a
Tehran hospital that the revolutionary leader was in excellent
condition.
   Khomeini has been reported ailing since he suffered a heart
attack in 1986. He has rarely been seen outside his home in
Tehran's Jamaran suburb.
   Official reports had listed Khomeini's age at 89, but his
brother Pasandideh said after the operation that Khomeini is 86.
