<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Boat     05-29 0095</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Boat,0098</SECOND>
<HEAD>Forty-one Drown When Boat Capsizes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An overloaded boat capsized in a river in
southern China, drowning at least 41 people, a news report said
Tuesday.
   The motorized junk, with a capacity of 60 people, was carrying
89 when it tipped over Monday about 130 feet from a river bank near
the city of Changsha, the official Xinhua News Agency reported.
   In addition to those known dead, two people were missing, the
report said.
   Last year, 386 people drowned in accidents on China's crowded
inland waterways, according to government figures.
