<TEXT>
   Singer Co. has been barred from selling any of
its assets or paying stock dividends pending a lawsuit over claims
that a former subsidiary defrauded the government.
   The company, named as a co-defendant in a civil suit against its
former Link Flight Simulation Division, was also ordered not to
incur any new debt or make any payments to investor Paul Bilzerian,
the Florida financier who acquired the company last year.
</TEXT>
