   General Foods USA has fired Ogilvy &amp; Mather as
the advertising agency for its Maxwell House coffee brand, which
Ogilvy has touted for 31 years as being ``Good to the last drop.''
   The food company said Friday that following a review of several
months it was awarding the account valued at more than $50 million
to D'Arcy Masius Benton &amp; Bowles, another New York-based ad agency.
